		  <div class="__pf" id="__pf"><div data-pf-type="Body" class="sc-pRgDJ fzXWJx pf-7faee9c1"><div data-pf-type="Layout" class="pf-d3927fae"><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-67fbaed6" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-2c51ac69 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-c02b2c51" data-pf-type="Column"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-278ebf23"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-d642278e">Frequently Asked Questions</span></h3><div data-pf-scrolltop="false" data-multiple="false" data-pf-type="Accordion2" class="sc-pkfPC jHjrlE pf-3a0ec02b"><div class="sc-pJipy mZVAk pf-4cf38df5 accordion__item" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content.Wrapper"><button type="button" class="sc-pBlxj gYSgcm pf-bf48f26f accordion__header pf-anchor" data-header-id="0dbf48f2-6f7b-4c4c-b38d-f53c873a0ec0" data-action="accordion2" data-preopen="false" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="icon_position accordion__arrow fa fa-chevron-right"></i>Products</button><div class="sc-qYUWV exYsxy pf-adae82b0 accordion__content" mode="view" data-id="0dbf48f2-6f7b-4c4c-b38d-f53c873a0ec0" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content" style="display: none;"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-535226e3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-5cdc5352"><span style="font-weight: bold;"><br>What makes UMA pads different?&nbsp;</span>For decades, pads have mostly been made the same way. The same chemically-processed, uncomfortable materials. And therefore, the same old problems:&nbsp;sweating, itching and that dreaded diaper feeling.<br><br>UMA is created to raise the standard of feminine care products. Our pads are made with ultra-soft organic cotton that are processed gently using oxygen instead of chlorine bleach. They are individually wrapped in oxo-biodegradable film and&nbsp;packed beautifully in fully-recycled boxes.<br><br><span style="font-weight: 700;">Why organic cotton? </span>Non-organic cotton is one of the dirtiest crops in the world. Grown using toxic pesticides and fertilisers, these cotton carry traces of chemicals that are harmful not only to us, but also to our soil and water.<br><br>Organic cotton is grown without any of these chemicals. As a result, it produces much cleaner product.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">What are the absorbency levels do these UMA offer?&nbsp;</span>UMA is available in Regular and Super size. UMA Regular is 24cm, designed for light to medium flow days. UMA Super is 29cm, designed for heavier flow.&nbsp;<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">How often should I change my pads?&nbsp;</span>We recommend changing your pads every 4 to 6 hours depending on your flow. When your flow is heaviest (usually at the beginning of your period), you may want to change more regularly to stay fresh. It is also good to change whenever you feel moisture to avoid bacterial build-up. <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Can I use these pads for incontinence? </span>Our&nbsp;pads were not designed specifically for incontinence, but some of our customers have used them for light bladder leaks.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;"> What does GOTS-certified mean? </span>The Global Organic Textile Standard (GOTS) is recognised as the gold standard of sustainable textile production. It ensures that the cotton we are using are&nbsp;grown organically, processed without harmful chemicals, and produced in a way that maintain efficient energy and water consumption, responsible waste management, and&nbsp;compliance with International Labour Standard. <br><br><span style="font-weight: 700;">What does recycled boxes actually mean?&nbsp;</span>This means putting back used fibres to the manufacturing system to create new fibres. By extending the lifetime of these fibres, we minimise the amount of waste going to the landfill and the demand for cutting down new trees. Our boxes are certified by Forest Stewardship Council (FSC).<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Are UMA pads biodegradable?&nbsp;</span>More than 90% component of UMA pads are designed to biodegrade in the landfill, whereas our boxes are 100% biodegradable.<br><br>Sustainable period care is at the core of our belief. If you are interested in reusable option, join our <span style="color: rgb(88, 123, 146);">waitlist</span> for an exclusive 20% discount on UMA menstrual cup.<br><br></span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pJipy mZVAk pf-8df53c87 accordion__item" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content.Wrapper"><button type="button" class="sc-pBlxj gYSgcm pf-f26f7b6c accordion__header pf-anchor" data-header-id="48f26f7b-6c4c-438d-b53c-873a0ec02b2c" data-action="accordion2" data-preopen="false" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="icon_position accordion__arrow fa fa-chevron-right"></i>Subscription</button><div class="sc-qYUWV exYsxy pf-b5b786b3 accordion__content" mode="view" data-id="48f26f7b-6c4c-438d-b53c-873a0ec02b2c" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content" style="display: none;"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-ad76d03f"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-f991ad76"><br><span style="font-weight: 700;">What is UMA subscription? </span>UMA subscription is an automated service that provides you personalised period care supply where and when you need it. It allows you to have high-quality period care when you need it, and saves you from&nbsp;those last-minute pharmacy run.<br><br><span style="font-weight: 700;">How does it work? </span>All you need to do is select the product assortment that you like and complete the order. We will deliver them to your door and send you a fresh set every 3 months, free of shipping. You can always change the product assortment,